      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KNOCKARD GIFT (5) is a talented type and proved too strong last time to win by a neck at Harlow in a handy 15.63 beating Mister Peevly. Has performed well from this box with a win and seven minor placings to her name from 16 starts. Great chance again. TULLYCANNA SADIE (4) has a strong record this trip with four wins and three placings from 12 starts. Scored by one length last time (15.52) in a IT over 238m at Harlow. Looks well placed here and among the chances. DA MOTOR MAN (2) jumped from this trap last time and placed in a IT at Harlow over 238m, finishing third (15.83). Has a very consistent record off this same box, including four wins and 11 placings from 20 starts. Worth following up. SPADE WORK (3) is down a grade after finishing fourth two starts back at Harlow then was again out of the placings at her latest appearance in a D3 at Harlow over 238m (15.64). Deserves another chance this class.",
